As we are planning to host a python web application, we are using flask which is a python web framework which is used to create python web applications.

# OS Type
Amazon Linux

# SG configuration
In your EC2 security configuration make sure port 80 is opened.

# Create a ec2 instance linux OS and switch as root user
sudo su

# Installing python
yum install python -y
python --version

# Creating a virtual environment for python
sudo yum install python3-pip
sudo pip3 install virtualenv
python3 -m virtualenv venv

# Activating the virtual environment
source venv/bin/activate

# Install flask
pip install flask

# Check flask version
Enter into python terminal (python >>>)
import importlib.metadata
print(importlib.metadata.version("flask"))
quit()
